  "body": "create this deamonset\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: extensions/v1beta1\r\nkind: DaemonSet\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: daemon-test\r\n  labels:\r\n    app: daemon-test\r\nspec:\r\n  selector:\r\n    matchLabels:\r\n      app: daemon-test\r\n  template:\r\n    metadata:\r\n      labels:\r\n        app: daemon-test\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n      - image: busybox\r\n        command:\r\n        - sleep\r\n        - \"36000\"\r\n        resources:\r\n          limits:\r\n            cpu: 200m\r\n            memory: 100Mi\r\n          requests:\r\n            cpu: 20m\r\n            memory: 20Mi\r\n      restartPolicy: Always\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith \r\n```console\r\n$ kubectl create -f daemonset.yaml\r\nerror: error validating \"/tmp/daemon.yaml\": error validating data: field name: is required; if you choose to ignore these errors, turn validation off with --validate=false\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich is a confusing error. \r\nThe code to change is: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/api/validation/validation.go#L1717\r\nIt can mention that path of the parent object missing the name. \r\n",
